{"lemma":"عَمَّةُ","slug":"عَمَّةُ","root":"ع.م.م","root_slug":"ع-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَمَّة","root":"عمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30456","n30457","n30602","n30604"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way of putting on the turban"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"turban","tags":["uncommon"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paternal blood aunt (one's father's sister)","examples":[{"text":"حُرِّمَتْ عَلَيْكُمْ أُمَّهَاتُكُمْ وَبَنَاتُكُمْ وَأَخَوَاتُكُمْ وَعَمَّاتُكُمْ[…]"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕim.ma/","/ʕam.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30456","headword_ar":"عَمَّةٌ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~N","text_ar":"عَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter, in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30457","headword_ar":"عِمَّةٌ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode of attiring oneself with the turban:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hasanu AlEim~api","text_ar":"هُوَ حَسَنُ العِمَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is comely in respect of the mode of attiring himself with the turban"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) ―         -b2-  [And it is vulgarly used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A turban"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaAmapN","text_ar":"عِمَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is used in this sense in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elm","text_ar":"علم"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealamotu Eim~atiY","text_ar":"عَلَمْتُ عِمَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"near the end of the first paragraph of that art.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30602","headword_ar":"عَمِهَ","root":"Emh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamaha","text_ar":"عَمَهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. of each"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamahN","text_ar":"عَمَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamohFA","text_ar":"عَمْهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK being a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamahFA","text_ar":"عَمَهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuwhN","text_ar":"عُمُوهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuwhapN","text_ar":"عُمُوهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamahaAnN","text_ar":"عَمَهَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) [the first of the former verb, and the rest, app., of the latter verb,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, and unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went repeatedly to and fro"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went repeatedly to and fro-"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in error, and confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unable to see his right course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,) in contending, disputing, or litigating; or in a way, or road: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he knew not the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"argument,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allegation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, K, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEAmh","text_ar":"تعامه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"signifies the same:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, K, TA:) all are said when one turns aside, or away, from that which is right, or true: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEamahu","text_ar":"العَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the looking repeatedly, not knowing whither to go:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA:) or it is in the mental perception; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEamaY","text_ar":"العَمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the sight, or is common to both of these. (TA.) [Accord. to the Msb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamiha","text_ar":"عَمِهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamohaA='","text_ar":"عَمْهَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to land, expl. below: but this requires consideration, as appears from what here follows.] ―         -b2-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamihati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"عَمِهَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land was destitute of signs of the way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) a tropical phrase. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Th","Z","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n30604","headword_ar":"عَمِهٌ","root":"Emh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAmihN","text_ar":"عَامِهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomahu","text_ar":"اَعْمَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In a state of confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexity, and unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going repeatedly to and fro:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going repeatedly to and fro,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in error, and confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unable to see his right course:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not knowing the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"argument,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allegation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [see 1:] pl. [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emihuwna","text_ar":"عمِهُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [of the second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eum~ahN","text_ar":"عُمَّهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) [and of the third"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumohN","text_ar":"عُمْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}